humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: Based on the rules provided and the pathology report, the patient has metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes, which corresponds to N1 (New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes). The report states 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae (No II/II) (NHG2, pT2, pNla)', indicating that 2 out of 2 assessed lymph nodes are positive for metastatic carcinoma, which falls within the criteria for N1.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae (No II/II) (NHG2, pT2, pNla)'. This indicates that there are cancerous metastases in the axillary lymph nodes. The Roman numerals II/II suggest that 2 out of 2 (or 100%) of the examined lymph nodes contain metastases. However, the N stage is not determined by the proportion of positive nodes, but rather by the number of positive nodes. Since there are metastases in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes, the N stage is N1.
